				<text>6.2.2.2 cosh^2-sinh^2</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise&nbsp;</p>
<p>We derive a fundamental identity relating hyperbolic functions&nbsp;<span class="math inline">\(\cosh^2x-\sinh^2x \equiv \ ?\)</span></p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
<li><p> First, express \(\cosh^2x\) in terms of the exponential functions. Expand your answer.</p>
<p>\(\cosh^2x \equiv \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p></li>
<li><p> Similarly, express \(\sinh^2x\) in terms of the exponential functions. Expand your answer.</p>
<p>\(\sinh^2x \equiv \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p></li>
<li><p> Finally determine <span class="math inline">\(\cosh^2x-\sinh^2x\)</span> using the results from (a) and (b):</p><p>\(\cosh^2x-\sinh^2x \equiv \) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Alternatively, we can prove the above identity by using the relations \(e^x \equiv \cosh x + \sinh x\) and \(e^{-x} \equiv \cosh x - \sinh x .\)
<p>See solution/feedback if you cannot work this out on your own.</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>Here is a step by step calculation.</p><p>\[ \begin{align*} \cosh^2x &amp; \equiv \left( {@cosh@} \right)^2 \equiv \frac{1}{4}(e^x+e^{-x})^2 \\ &amp; \equiv \frac{1}{4}[(e^x)^2+2e^xe^{-x}+(e^{-x})^2] \equiv \frac{1}{4}[e^{2x}+2e^{x-x}+e^{-2x}] \\ &amp; \equiv {@cosh2@} .\end{align*} \]</p><p>\[ \begin{align*} \sinh^2x\ &amp; \equiv \left( {@sinh@} \right)^2 \equiv \frac{1}{4}(e^x-e^{-x})^2 \\ &amp; \equiv \frac{1}{4}[(e^x)^2-2e^xe^{-x}+(e^{-x})^2] \equiv \frac{1}{4}[e^{2x}-2e^{x-x}+e^{-2x}] \\ &amp; \equiv&nbsp; {@sinh2@}. \end{align*} \]</p><p>Alternatively, using \(e^x \equiv \cosh x + \sinh x\) and \(e^{-x} \equiv \cosh x - \sinh x \), we obtain \[1 \equiv e^x \cdot e^{-x} \equiv (\cosh x + \sinh x)(\cosh x - \sinh x) \equiv \cosh^2x - \sinh^2x \] as desired.</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
